SUPER Eagles striker, Taiwo Awoniyi is being courted by Premier League clubs and has become the subject of a £25m move. According to GOAL, the former Liverpool attacker’s splendid performances at Union Berlin is catching the eye in England and he may be making a move pretty soon if the money is deemed too good to be rejected.   BREAKING: Full group draws of Qatar 2022 World Cup     Davido features on 2022 World Cup official theme song     Fernandes extends Man United contract   West Ham, Southampton, and Newcastle have been listed as potential destinations for the attacker who was on Liverpool’s books for six years without kicking a ball. He went on seven loan spells and the last was a major stint as he did enough to convince the capital club to splash £6.5m to tie him down.